#: src/ch13-02-iterators.md:75
msgid "// methods with default implementations elided\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/ch13-02-iterators.md:79
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Notice that this definition uses some new syntax: `type Item` and "
"`Self::Item`, which are defining an associated type with this trait. We’ll "
"talk about associated types in depth in Chapter 20. For now, all you need to "
"know is that this code says implementing the `Iterator` trait requires that "
"you also define an `Item` type, and this `Item` type is used in the return "
"type of the `next` method. In other words, the `Item` type will be the type "
